Package sk.uisav.icontrol

Class StitcherClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • sk.uisav.icontrol.StitcherClient
  • public class StitcherClient
extends java.lang.Object
    Client for the stitching process, contains higher-level methods working in the logic of the stitching process and abstracting from WebDAV technicalities. Use: 1. create an instance of sk.uisav.icontrol.WebDavClient 2. create an instance of sk.uisav.icontrol.StitcherClient using the WebDavClient as an argument 3. use the StitcherClient's methods to get/put your data

      • StitcherClient

        public StitcherClient​(WebDavClient wdclient,
                      java.lang.String huginFormat)
        Creates new Stitcher client instance based on already initialized WebDAV client object
        Parameters:
        wdclient - already initialized WebDAV client
        huginFormat - the format of file naming used by the hugin step to name created panormamas. Default value is '/Microstep/hugin/result/panasonic_fullhd_01-090-000-'yyyyMMddHHmm' - panasonic_fullhd_01-090-315-'yyyyMMddHHmm'.jpg' The default value is used in this parameter is null. If you provide your own value, it must conform to the @see SimpleDateFormat formatting conventions.
